2️⃣ Chemical Road Fingerprinting 🧪
Concept: Molecular Surface Analysis

Current safety systems only detect if a road is slippery; IVSCS aims to identify why it is slippery by analyzing the road’s chemical composition in real-time.

The Technology: Utilizing Nano-electromechanical Systems (NEMS), the tire surface acts as a distributed mass spectrometer, identifying the Molecular Signature of various substances.

The Mechanism: The system distinguishes between H2O (water), crystalline structures (Black Ice), and complex hydrocarbons (Oil/Fuel spills) instantly upon contact.

The Impact: This data is synchronized with a Cloud-based Hazard Map, enabling "Collaborative Safety" where one vehicle warns an entire fleet of a specific chemical hazard at a precise GPS coordinate.

