3️⃣ Bio-Inspired Self-Healing Circuitry 🧬
Concept: Adaptive Longevity & Regeneration

The most significant challenge for embedded tire sensors is physical degradation. IVSCS solves this by mimicking biological tissue regeneration.

The Technology: A Microfluidic Sensor Architecture consisting of a network of microscopic reservoirs and channels embedded deep within the tread layers.

The Mechanism: As the tire tread wears down and a sensor terminal is severed, the internal pressure change triggers the release of a Conductive Liquid Polymer. This material flows to the surface and solidifies upon contact with air, instantly forming a new, functional sensor probe.

The Impact: This ensures that the tire’s "Digital Sense of Touch" remains at 100% sensitivity from the day of manufacture until the tire reaches its legal wear limit.

